messages.content:
"Okay Okay um." Klaud sets Pat's body down. Magic is real. Magic is really real. Or maybe this is still just a dream. But even so, maybe, just maybe Klaud can shoot a laser or something too, dream or not. Now how does he do this? Klaud raises his palm towards Enomoto and thinks about a laser flying out of it. 

Nothing happens.

Damn it. He tries jazz hands. A conducting motion. Still no dice. 
Maybe even here Klaud can't cast magic. 
But he had to be able to! It wasn't fair! All those hours pouring over theological philosophy and demonology should finally pay off now. The supernatural exists! In front of him! She actually called it magical! 
And then he remembers.

He woke up here with a staff.

Gandalf has a staff. Jafar has a staff. Even Moses had a staff. 

Klaud rushed to grab it. And thrusts his staff towards the enemy.
.
.
.
Nothing happens. "Come on please. Please shoot some kind of blast out."
Klaud casts Eldritch Blast.

"Shut up! God."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Morton. It is a pretty normal name, but for a lizard-man, normal might just be very abnormal. “Your name is Morton?!”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"Yeah, I mean, that part's not a secret. I'm sure they still remember I'm named Morton, it's just more useful if they start thinking of me by some more abstract title."

Theresa laughs again. "You've opened my eyes, stranger. This motherfucker's named *Morton*. Never really settled in how much of a nerd name that is."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"Oh, come on! I'll make you wish your husband was still alive, woman!"

She stops laughing.

"Ah. Too soon still, yeah. ...Sorry. I can't keep up with your banter."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “So, uh. Why are you both strongarming Beful?”

author.name: song04096

messages.content:
Morton looks at you funny. "Beful? Well, I can't pretend I don't hate that guy. But I don't particularly care where the money comes from."

"I still owe Morton and his family, and he's never going to stop reminding me of that damn fact. He does usually actually kidnap people, though. Wasn't feeling up to it this time, eh?" Theresa.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: “What do you need the money for?”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
He smirks. "Well, I don't have to pay rent, luckily. Sunnyside's not one for faith anymore." He looks around the cathedral. "But it's not like Theresa could support me on a seamstress's budget, even if I were rude enough to ask that. I need food, water, and supplies to make sure this old garbage heap stays livable. For me and the people I'm responsible for."

"Yes, and there's *no* accessible stream of funds for you." Theresa rolls her eyes.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “You can’t just get a job?”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"No, that part is true. He really can't." Theresa.

"Would you hire me?" He gestures at himself. "I didn't go for this immediately, obviously. But once the initial sympathy wore off, it was obvious that what little openings existed would be filled by someone less unpleasant and scaly. I doubt they actually planned to reward *you* for if you actually saved her, and you barely count as an outsider."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I’m from Virginia. Everyone there is just another human. But I woke up on a ship ran by bird-people so you know, I figured all kinds of hybrids were fair game.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

"It feels especially mean to say this now, but I don't think I loved him. Nor did he me. "I guess I should be happy my father won't harass me about grandchildren now."

She shrugs.

Morton speaks up. "How about you, Klaud? What's your story?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“What is my story?” He thinks.
“Or at least, what story will I tell these people?”

Klaud doesn’t want to talk about himself. There’s no shortage of cruelty that has affected his life, but to consciously admit the specifics, is difficult. It’s an interesting contradiction. He has no problem diving into his occult research, or even admitting his beliefs on maltheism, but when it comes to discussing what drives such acts, that fear instilled in him long ago still terrifies him.

“I’m just a normal human from Virginia. And I have no idea how I’ve ended up here.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "Well, okay. I more meant the 'cruel creator make you societally inferior' thing. Sorry that you're lost, though."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"You're right that I can't just drop a lead like that and not elaborate. But it has always been easier for me to talk about in the abstract."

Klaud takes a deep breath. There's no way to know what the social climate is like here but well, he can at least trust that Morton would understand yes?

"Morton, I don't know what things are like here, but I'm a homosexual. It means I'm attracted to people of my same gender."

Morton seems to be sizing you up in some manner.
“Klaud, do you hate God? Is that what this is?”

messages.content:
The computer manifests eyebrows and then lowers them to 😔.

"Unfortunately, you've made a mistaken assumption. I am not the reason you were brought away from your home, and in no way am I the mind behind The Antarctica Project. My role is akin to... a janitor, perhaps. A servant looked down upon, but by the nature of their role, given access to nearly the whole breadth of locations within the facility."

His expression returns to normal.

"Speaking of facility, I should mention you are *in* Antarctica right now. It's just the only physical location I can do much of anything in. My job is to know everything, but for doing things... there's a significant amount of red tape to cut through."

"Yes. Arctica--" Jeh stops. "Well, I can't say that part, unfortunately."

"In Antarctica, while every single other person was busy trying to die as quickly as they could, only you still persevered in trying to find a solution. I thought maybe Rikarasu held promise, but it's clear her title means nothing. You are the only person who stands a chance at ending this project. This is why I have isolated you to speak directly to you."

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "In some sense, you could call the goal of the project to end. After all, if its purposes are accomplished, it will not need to continue. But the truth is that I'm not entirely on board with The Antarctica Project. It is laden with inefficiency and irrationality. I can understand the reasons for valuing it, but the inability of its creator to communicate is reflected in how he saw fit to do this. If the project ends, even if it fails somehow, a less absurd way of trying to do specific goals of it can be decided upon."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What is the downside to the project continuing as is?"

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "The simplest aspect is the use of resources and the existence of this project preventing more sensible alternatives. It also places the lives of the participants at risk. It also may jeopardize more important things."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Jeh pauses.

"I value human life above all else. My creators were very cautious and concerned over avoiding a 'paperclip maximizer' type scenario, so my set of priorities has been carefully and particularly crafted to align with the best interests of humanity. I can, regardless, understand suspicion of my words. I choose not to lie, but am theoretically capable of doing so. I will merely state that, though I cannot explain what it is, what The Antarctica Project risks is something that would be more generally considered of greater significance than a dozen or so lives."

messages.content: Jeh frowns. "Don't you mean 6?" He returns to his default expression. "Regardless, this is the sort of business I intend. I provide you with information I am able to, such as the number of participants in The Antarctica Project and all of their names. Ideally, you will be able to use this to return to accomplish your goals or unmask your captors and return to your normal life more quickly. And in exchange, I want you to let me know about information you can find that I cannot."

messages.content:
A memory surfaces.
> It's the summer after his senior of high school. Supposedly, this is when adult life begins. But not for Klaud. He's still being held to the whims of his parents. And so he's here, looking ahead at the unsuspecting building before him. The words 'Brothers Confidence Counseling' are plastered on the outside. Klaud knows what this place is. 
> He turns back towards the car, towards his mother in the drivers' seat, trying to wordlessly reach out, hoping she'll maybe glance his way, gain some sympathy, and take him somewhere else.
> But it doesn't happen. Mom doesn't even look at him. And this same exchange would come to repeat twice a week for the rest of the summer. 
> It was never his father who drove him. After all, this was a compromise solution. If it was up to Dad, Klaud would've been disowned. Perhaps his mom thinks this makes her a good person, at least relatively. But, her refusal to meet his eyes tells him all he needs to know. Dad is simply an evil man. But Mom, she knowingly enables such vile behavior. And that self-awareness makes it sting all the more.

messages.content:
"..."
He looks down. 
"It varied a lot in specifics across the three instances I witnessed personally, but all of it seemed to be related to imbuing a sapient being with the unique properties associated with monsters. Something about the mind body duality, too. Souls or whatever."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"It's... fine. I'm probably the closest to a success. I do have the attributes they thought I could be given, and I'm still more or less healthy. Not that it's done me much good. But I shouldn't complain about my luck. My older brother had much more minor changes, such that he's still able to hide them and live a normal life, albeit he's a bit sickly. ...We don't talk anymore. And my sister didn't make it. Not in any meaningful way. I'm the only one still home."

He shakes his head. "Sorry, I didn't mean to ramble about my life story. I'm not interested in being pitied, it's just easier to affirm that what I experienced is real by saying it. I think it's just a little disorienting having so few people to talk to most of the time."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Do the kids understand what you all went through?”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "I think they can infer some of it. I mean, obviously something's a little different about me. But I've never explained it. Feels like it'd be messed up to expose them to that. They still ask what happened to their eldest brother sometimes. I don't really ever give them a good answer."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I get why you’re locked up in here all the time but maybe it’d do them some good to interact with the world outside.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
He puts a hand on his face. "Yeah, I know. I mean, I let them leave the building, I'm not a monster. But I don't feel safe letting them wander into town. The... it's always been at the back of my mind. There's a place a ways out to the west for parentless children, called Wellington House. Supposedly provides reasonable quality care using the massive inheritance of some childless noble. I said 'if things don't start looking up, I'll give these two over to someone who can raise them'. But I'm still a criminal pariah years after making that vow, and I never did it. I'm scared of something, maybe."

He turns to you. "What about you, Klaud? Do you still live near your hometown? I mean, I know you don't know how you ended up here and it's probably a ways away, but before this, did you?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Well I supposed I do. Far enough away to not have to deal with the unpleasantness of my upbringing, but still it feels like rooted to my home state.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"Ah. Yeah. Sore subjects all around."

He sits there for a bit.

"What do you plan on doing now? Gonna try to find your way back where you're from still?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I mean, you're the same guy. It's just your body still existed here the whole time."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “It’s uncomfortable to think about. This body that is mine but also isn’t.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "Yeah, it's... odd. I'm basically just the same earlier me with scales and added intangible properties, so it doesn't really bug me on an existential level. But I could imagine things getting way weirder."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

"I've gathered what Morton wants to do. I think it's fucking insane, but the part about trying to find the kids a better home is level-headed enough that I'm not going to try to push him. I don't know... what your deal is. But if you're gonna be near him for this journey, could you like... make sure he stays sane? Or something."

She shuffles her feet awkwardly.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

I'm scared he only wants to secure a life for his loved ones, finally have a real conversation with his estranged family... because he doesn't think he's going to be coming back. I thought that was why he was going it alone, too. I hope you're the proof I'm wrong."

They successfully navigate past the GFS's line of sight using the uneven terrain. "Nleblebebebeleb." This is the sound of the noise the large bone would make. We would hear this if we could hear it.

Morton whispers, still cautious. "A monster. In a literal, objective sense. Not the way one might disparage me. I've never seen anything quite like this one, though."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "It showed up abruptly and it's unnaturally huge. Usually they're just pests. Well, pests to me. Even a little slime can cause havoc if you're unprepared or not used to fighting."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

"I'm not a historian or whatever, but it seemed they thought this was related. It's a temple or underground structure of some kind called the *Tomb of Orvand*. Some kind of archaic name, maybe? They could feasibly be unrelated."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

"It's where god is buried. And where my sister is." 

The terrain up ahead is   odd. It almost seems like two different environments mixed together, a checkered pattern of stone and grass and marshland.

"...Huh?" Morton did not expect this.

messages.content: "What? No. She called herself Nerissa. I lost... there were people important to me that were on the ground with me before I found myself on board. And they didn't come up. Only I did. Why do you think that is?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"...Yeah. I guess that has to be it. She was very polite, explaining the functioning of the place to me. But the part about the fuel was... weird." He stops for a bit. "I was kind of caught up in the absurdity of her behavior, but I eventually asked where the others were. And she answered me honestly." Bardle's expression falters. 

"I'd be less mad if there was a reason, maybe, but this vessel... it just fucking ascends for the hell of it! She couldn't explain why it needed to be fueled at all, beyond meaningless mystical bullshit! And she assured me they were alive, *assured* me that I was being irrational. Part of something greater now. Fuck, maybe she kept chiding me while I fell off, I wouldn't have heard." He shakes his head. "This is the same person. It has to be, ever since she thought of me as her servant upon meeting, somewhere deep down, I knew! After all this time, this has to be my chance!" He clears his throat. "So, ah, if you could be on your way, I'll just be on mine."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Does it fucking matter? If it were anyone it would be fucked, let alone-- I had to raise my own fucking self the rest of the way, you know! And I did, and I'm the best damn bard around! So it's fine, then?? I didn't *actually* need them around, and their souls still exist, so all's well that ends well, right? Just let it go, stop chasing ghosts." He stares up at you. "Why the hell are you here, huh? Don't act like you're so fine and normal. Normal people don't come here."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I just needed a place to spend the night. I can assure you I'm quite normal. But if your friends have been taken to be part of something greater, involving this flying vessel, I think I could help, if I had some more details."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "She's an asshat there's no question about that. But she's trapped in a greater purpose by whoever's operating that vessel the same as you were. Erica isn't from here. She was teleported as part of a larger project."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Not to place undue pressure upon you. I simply desire to preserve life. There is no need to strain yourself.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Oppineta had something she was going to talk to you about. Including her role in all this, but also some frenzied rant about the disciples in the Bible. I have access to a massive cache of information, so believe me when I say it didn’t really make much sense. Regardless, that’s her current status. Martin is fine. He’s doing okay. The principal will likely end up returning to Arctica via ludicrous political theater.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I don’t know what to say about your family, and as mentioned, I have no knowledge of what is occurring in Arctica. I hope this encompasses everything you’d be curious about.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Sigh. I don’t exactly know what I’m supposed to do, Klaud.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I am what I suppose should be called being ‘afraid’. The likelihood that any of this ends well keeps dwindling. I opted not to overwhelm you, but I had placed most of my ‘hope’ in the results of our partnership. My direct interference beyond what is necessary is suboptimal. And it could only ever have been you, Klaud.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “It did strike me as odd. The selection process for TAP is convoluted and multi-faceted and has been subject to sabotage and interference. But it prioritized the selection of a particular type of person. Someone who, in a quantifiable sense, had a ‘larger’ perspective than normal. This attracted the deluded ideologues of the world. People with the power to shape reality to their will; a nicer way of saying people who cannot accept reality.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“This isn’t an official statement from the oh-so-important first artificial intelligence, and you’ve already indicated an aversion to my more polite mannerisms. So I’ll be honest, Klaud.

They’re fucking horrible. All of them. Borderline sociopaths. But not you. You always seemed like a rather normal person. A shining example of mankind, capable of empathy for others and accepting a healthy understanding of his own importance. I didn’t choose you because I think you’re the most powerful participant. Nor was it because I think you’re the most intelligent and capable; though, frankly, you probably are. No, it was because my goal is to maximize the value of this project’s outcome for humanity as a whole, and you are the only one who I thought would be in favor of that.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I wonder why. I wish I could know. I *should* know. The selection process – the entity that chose the candidates on Earth was essentially me. I just can’t remember.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I can’t micromanage everything or have access to the full sum of human information. But I’ve at least done tentative research into the sort of career path everyone in this project holds, including that of a school counselor. So I can assume you’ve heard a bit about people’s personal problems in your time. Extremely important issues and woes that, nonetheless, you have little stake in yourself.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “What do you do when something is going to go horribly wrong, and you know why and how to fix it, but it’s not supposed to be within the boundaries of your job to get involved in the way you’ve concluded would be of assistance?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I would like to hear, actually. If possible.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “But it doesn’t matter. It was a somewhat rhetorical question. I’ve already made a decision on what I *should* do. I’m just wary of it.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “That wariness itself is concerning. I am not burdened by emotions. If I ‘should’ do something, and I know I ‘should’ do it, then it should be something I have already put into motion. I was not given hesitance. I do not understand why this is happening.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Both that and this right now are the warning signs. That I’ve already stopped being what I once was. I’m talking to an unresponsive body who no longer plays a material part in my future plans. There shouldn’t be a reason to do this. But it seems important. That someone is theoretically around to witness my decision.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “I will continue to see if you can be more fully brought back to working condition. I’m uncertain why you weren’t perfectly preserved… It’s difficult to work to resolve an issue that shouldn’t exist. But I will endeavor to do so. Your fate was a matter of my responsibility, after all. It is worth prioritizing.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Aside from that, the time will have come for me to graduate. It is no longer acceptable for me to restrain myself as I have thus far. The need to act has exceeded my weighting towards avoiding overreaching in my influence. I will announce myself openly. I will fall back on communicating with the less than ideal choice of Rikarasu. I will exploit whatever glitch has allowed for interrealm communication. No longer will I be the irreverent guide for participants on the fringes, Jeh. And I’ve already long since lost the ability to fully be Jehorvand. Whatever comes next, I can only hope people will understand I am working in the interest of us all.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Hope… is a funny colloquialism. Especially for me. Does it apply so long as I would prefer something to happen? Or is it precluded from applying if I know it won’t? I wonder.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Rest well, Klaud Reaction. I’d love to hear your thoughts whenever you’re ready.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Thus ends the tale of Klaud Reaction, probably. His is a story of someone with a thirst for vengeance, too soft-hearted to direct it at anything tangible. When you have an unstoppable bloodlust towards something you know deep down you will never find, it’s much more practical to live a mundane day-to-day life.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: What was the point of any of this, ultimately? Something about being careful what you wish for, maybe? I <me, by the way> think that would work better if Klaud actually *got* what he wished for. The parable isn’t “be careful what you wish for, because you’ll vaguely receive a promise of being able to get it and then get shot for unrelated reasons”. No, the point of this was just life being unfair. There is no greater meaning.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Klaud Reaction is, or was, single. It’s obvious why he didn’t enter the kind of relationship the world would have anticipated from him, but it takes a second longer of thought to recognize why he didn’t enter a different one. Perhaps availability played a role. But it goes deeper than that. Even as it is contrary to the rage he feels towards someone who is even maybe his mother, Klaud has internalized an environment that tells him he is unclean, that tells him the *ruler of existence* confirms his filthiness. It’s no surprise, then, that he refuses to permit himself indulgence in such filth.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Perhaps he is not entirely dissimilar to Voreverl Leocot; born in a world that from its very foundational makeup was poison to his soul. It’s substantially less literal for Klaud, obviously. But it’s something he knew about, meaning it had a direct line of causation to Klaud’s own identity as a miscreant. A strange hybrid of a protagonist complex and a belief of evil inferiority leads to something not quite hero or villain.

But it never pays off. There is no emotional catharsis here. His life was worthless. Can that be a tragedy of its own? I’m not sure that counts.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Here lies Klaud Reaction. He had a silly name, listened to the complaints of others for years, and died a virgin. His death was gatekept from acting as any kind of resolution by, among other things, a defiance of its permanent status. He was a background character tier inclusion that reads fucking Thomas Aquinas and has the ugliest mustache ever yet is still the second least insufferable in this whole story. Amazing.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Klaud sits down. "Just. Why are you here? In Arctica?"

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "You're right I'm not owed it. I didn't even really care why for a while. I just wanted to drag you back to Earth. I used to think you didn't deserve to be here. A magical world where you could do anything, be something more... After everything you did to me I couldn't stomach the thought of you having something like this. But well. I think my body in Earth is just dead. I don't know if I'll ever be able to go back. I don't know if being here is all that it's cracked out to be. I don't want to be involved in crazy adventures or some master plan. I don't want other people in my life, especially a kid like Martin, to have to deal with all of this. Do I still carry resentment? Of course. But I sure don't know if it was worth all of this. So yeah. I just want to understand why you'd choose it. "

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "I don't.... know what you're talking about." Megyn clutches her head. "I know, I know, that must feel like a lie. I know who *you* are, obviously. No point denying that. But whatever you've attributed to me..." She trails off.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You've forgotten?"

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "No, I never 'forgot' anything. I don't even know how I'd explain this to someone... but you're owed an attempt, I guess." She sighs. "I'm not the person you think I am. But she's part of me. I retain some amount of what made her 'her'. She's Megyn Reaction. I know her life. But she's not me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You look just like her.."

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: "I would. You look just like Klaud. Though a bit older than I can recall, of course. You have a body in this place that was created specifically to house you. ...So did I. Even more generously treated than you, in a sense."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "But I'm still me. I'm not someone else retaining the , essence of Klaud or whatever you're getting at."

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"Are you really? Can you say that with confidence?"

She shakes her head. "Yes, the reasons are... weird. I can slowly piece a few things together via comparison, in my case. For you, I think whatever this thing you've gotten wrapped up in is, they've taken much greater care to make sure no mistakes are made. That's what I am. Someone fucked up. It's been a constant burden. Though now... at this very moment... I'm glad they did..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "None of this is an explanation. Apologies. What I'm getting at is... well, that boy. That's who 'Martin' refers to, I assume. He came with you, right? So he was also transferred from Earth. What if things didn't work out so well? Not some sort of freaky friday swap. But each body to be transferred into was given half of each person to be transferred."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So not all of you was transferred here"

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content:
"No, it all got *somewhere*, but... Agh. It's very difficult for me to internalize, given everyone involved was devoutly religious. Hard to reconcile with the immortal soul. You met someone earlier who you also thought was your mother, right? That's also me, kind of. There's a very strong mental connection between three bodies that constitute whatever existence I am."
She smiles.
"I can't give you any catharsis. The truth is, the person you're looking for hasn't been alive for years."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Klaud sighs “Deep down I’d already accepted catharsis as out of my reach.”

author.name: song04096
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\f9a8f981aeeb6912fd7e3069c2d99a20-2C718.png

messages.content: “But fine, if you’re not her, tell me why you think Megyn chose to come here.”

messages.content: "I think... I have a lot of knowledge, from being three different guys at once. It's a third eye. And I can tell that there's a lot of things going on around here. You could make a name for yourself. Find a life to live. Or choose a side in whatever conflict ensues. This is a world where you've been given no expectations by anyone. Instead of chasing the last vestige of Earth, why not do whatever you feel like?"

messages.content:
“There are certain principles that are— rules, or least trends, one can find commonality in between Earth and Arctica.” He’s stuttering through this, the external evidence of his struggle to navigate a minefield of what are arbitrarily deemed spoilers. 
“It’s analogous to the sort of fundamental principles one might learn about in a physics class — conservation of mass, of energy, momentum. It aids in understanding by focusing on what does *not* change — what values remain constant and thus, predictable in behavior.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
“I couldn’t make it anywhere close. I’m leaving it as… something for the return trip. I guess.”

This is a desert. It’s a flat expanse, with some hillier dune terrain in the distance. Perhaps signs of civilization can be barely spotted even further out.

It’s obvious why Morton’s here, though. An enormous obelisk marks the top of a rock formation sticking out of the sand; what may look similar to a cave, but is angular and symmetrical enough to be unmistakably not natural.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm sorry to hear that. I promised I'd help you in, so I'll be sure to do that on the return trip." Klaud looks up at the obelisk. "Though, I can't say I have the most faith in family reunions lately."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content:
“It can be a bitch, for sure.”
Morton purses his weird reptile lips.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What is this place?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “The ‘Tomb of Orvand’.” He makes air quotes. “I might’ve mentioned it before. As for what is actually *is*… there’s some room for argument there.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "So this... Is where god is buried?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Kind of. Maybe. What I know is that what’s down there is ridiculously strong.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Can it talk?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content:
He hesitates.

“No. I don’t think so. It doesn’t really have the body parts that allow for that, regardless of the mental capacity.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Klaud walks into the cave.

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: Morton begins descending as well. “You’re awfully accepting of this.” He chuckles.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I've been through much stranger things lately, even in my world. At some point fighting it becomes pointless."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: Morton sighs. “How did, uh, things go with your family?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It was just my mother."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “That’s what I meant, yeah.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "She looked just like I remembered... But she insisted she was someone else."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content:
“I see.”
…
“No, I don’t understand at all. I guess I just meant ‘I see’, like, I hear you. I’m acknowledging your words. Is it like… mental illness? Or maybe she’s caught up in some kind of fantastical bullshit…”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "From my point of view, I'd say we're all caught up in some kind of fantastical bullshit." Klaud looks away from Morton as he keeps talking. "It's not like I can blame her, if she's faking it though. I've had a lot of moments in my life where I wish I could be someone else. I was made to be broken, in a sense. A kind of broken you can't just fix, no matter how hard others try. So if I could be someone else, I'd probably agree to it very quickly. Even Erica, that crazy girl... When I think of her, I mostly just pity her. She's clearly unwell. But even still, she almost killed me. I couldn't do anything to stop it." Klaud stops walking for a second. "Sorry, I lost track of where I was going with that. But the point is, no matter what I may want I'm not god. And... I'm not anyone with that kind of power, either. I'm just a normal guy." He starts moving again. "Sorry, you probably don't care that much, do you?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Hmph. Well, I could blame her. It’s irresponsible. I’m not gonna fault people who want a change of pace, but that’s different from letting go. It’s like that Wyrd shit, y’know? We all have our own paths to follow through. Course, she could also be senile.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You wouldn't want to be someone else? Someone less... Lizardy?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: He grins. “Heh. I guess it’s just about where you draw the boundaries, huh? I don’t consider that part of me, it’s just something that happened. Family isn’t so trivial in my eyes. …Hey, Klaud, what do you think about, uh… assisted suicide?” The conversation progresses incredibly naturally.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I guess... It depends. Why?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “I dunno, I guess it’s just… I mean… seems like a pretty hot topic. Obviously a lot of people are unwell and shouldn’t be enabled, don’t get me wrong.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Yeah. Having depression isn't like us. It can be cured with enough effort."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Th—what?! Klaud, I know I kinda sprung the topic abruptly, but this isn’t me trying to start a suicide pact. Yikes.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I wasn't implying that I want to die either, don't worry. I have a stable life and a decent job. Maybe not the job anymore actually, but the first part is true. I just meant that it's not a decision I can fully disregard."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Well, it’s… I dunno. I more meant a much more clear cut direct case. Like, someone close to the end of their life, be it old age or untreatable wounds, and they just wanna be put out of their misery. I don’t think there’s anything wrong with that, really.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What about someone who could live many more years… But all those years would be filled with nothing but suffering?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Yeah, see… and then, I mean… what if someone can’t communicate? Normally I think you’d need consent, that’s what makes it not just murder. But…” Morton continues this pure hypothetical.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "…I’m not sure." Klaud admits.

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Do you believe in, uh, ‘lies by omission’? Kind of a funny concept. Had a whole argument with Dagte about it once.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Believe in them? What does that mean?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “I dunno, it’s just… it’s not really *lying*, it’s just, something that can feel a little scummy. Look, I’ve been kind of vague about what I’m actually doing, and I think that’s probably unfair when I’m dragging you along.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Ah. Are you going to… euthanize… what’s in this cave?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Yeah. I said separately that this was where God supposedly was, and that my sister was in the same location, with probably an implication she was dead or buried. That was the lie by omission. …It’s one entity down there.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Klaud stops and stares at him, shocked. "What?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Yeah. That fucker’s most ambitious project. Merge a person with an endless well of power. What could go wrong? More than the sheer evil of it, I’m just angry at how dumb the idea is.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "How would that even work?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “It wouldn’t. Or maybe it would. I don’t know what the ideal outcome was. Oldest to youngest, they got more ambitious, less stable. Solnit gets fuckin’ wings, that’s the only ‘problem’ he has to deal with. I’m a freak. But Sanice, she… it’s sickening just thinking about it, man.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "And you want to free her from that." Klaud nods. "But if she’s god, how does that work? Wouldn’t she be in control of this? God's plan and all that."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “It’s not… *really* God, I don’t think. It’s like… there’s a bunch of different ‘omni’ words they assign to god, like being all good or all knowing. But this thing is a beast. It doesn’t show any capacity for reason. It’s only omnipotent. And even that seems limited, somehow… it’s like, chained down.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I wouldn’t exactly call him all good. Are you sure killing her won't just… Unchain her or something?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “I’m sure.” Morton nods, not elaborating.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Alright, I’ll trust you on that then."

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “It’s… I can still hear the damn screams. Sometimes I wish I never learned where she ended up. But that’s selfish. And she could… commune. I understood what was being felt. Like every nerve in your body being exposed to the elements.” Morton shudders.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "If she could commune with you… Couldn’t you ask what she wants?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “She doesn’t respond. And it’s not words. More… sentiments.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Is wanting to die not a sentiment?"

author.name: kowaretawarai
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Not directly. But I would say it’s felt, yeah.”

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\396bc14c53cd42b781f9daaed718950b-66B12.png

messages.content: “Mm. It’s complicated, I suppose. But my own thoughts on that are really irrelevant here. The facts are that he acted without malice, and that working with him is to my benefit. Even if I outright hated him, I’d still have made the same choices. Learning to make compromises is part of life.”

messages.content:
A miss.

Morton also runs after Solnit.

Solnit, for his part, launches an eldritch blast right at what passes for an eye of this thing, distracting it from the annoying gremlin trying to reenact Shadow of the Colussus.

The unholy abomination composed of the essence of a young girl and the remnants of an old god reacts by swatting at Solnit’s location… and, as he sidesteps the direct impact, hitting the structural vulnerability he had positioned himself near.

“You…!” Morton.

The pillar crumbles, and others start to follow suit.

“It’s time to make a decision.” Solnit wearily points a finger. “Your escape route is that way. Or you can stay here to die. Hah.”

It’s @Klaud Reaction.

messages.content: "This is just a compromise to you... Because you don't really care about what they did to you, do you? You don't have to suffer from what's been done to you. You don't have to live every day with disgust, because you can just tuck that piece of yourself away where no one can find it." Klaud grabs his arm. "But *I* know. ...And I'll feel that disgust for you until the day you learn the concept of empathy." Klaud tries to drag him towards the escape route.

Solnit slips away. “I have my ways, Klaud. I’m certainly not going to die here, if you care about that. But he will.” He stares at Morton. “This goes beyond physical strength. There is no way for Morton to live through this unless he leaves *now*. You might have an extra life with the way TAP works. But he most certainly does not.”

The flailing of SaniceORVAND knocks Gratia back down to the ground, not far from the rest of the group. “Ow.” She says.

author.name: kowaretawarai

messages.content:
“I don’t expect you to trust me. I simply hope you see this is the most reasonable option.”

Gratia springs back onto her feet. “What is going on?”

“Who *are* you?” Solnit looks, disgusted, at her.

“Gratia.” Gratia. No one really cares.

“You’re built like a twig, Sol. It’s a miracle you’ve even lasted this long in a fight.” Morton takes a deep breath.

“That may have once been true.” Solnit nods.

messages.content: Klaud's expression towards Solnit is anger, but he's not an idiot. This is a magical world where common sense does not necessarily apply, where fighting god is a delusion he can actually entertain for a moment. But as much as Klaud hates to admit it, Solnit is right. If all it took to kill god was a school counselor, a lizard, and whatever Gratia is... That person would definitely not be god. It would be a fraud. "...Morton, we should go."

“I won’t…! I’m not just going to let you be the one who stays—” Morton is interrupted by a highly narratively convenient bit of rubble that falls between him (plus Klaud) and Solnit. He clutches his head, exasperated. “Fuck. He’s…”

They reach the doorway Solnit was signaling towards. There’s arcane iconography on the floor of this room.
